# Becker / Lychee S3 data lake (handoff context)

Use this when changing **S3 uploads**, **manifests**, or the **data-lake Parquet API**. The Next.js UI + DuckDB pipelines live elsewhere; this rule is **storage and ingestion** only.

## Primary script

- **`scripts/publish-becker-both-parquet-to-s3-stream-extract.js`**
  - **Flow**: HTTP download `data.tar.zst` (default Becker URL) → `zstd -d` → `tar-stream` → **one S3 `PutObject` per `.parquet`** (no full local extract of the whole archive).
  - **Phases**: `[1]` stream pipeline → `[2/3]` stream pass complete (upload counts / skipped) → optional S3 listing sample → `[3/3]` write **local** JSON manifests under `.tmp-becker-manifest/` → **upload manifests** to S3.
  - **`Done.`** means the script finished without throw; manifests were uploaded (unless `--dry-run`).

## Completeness report

- **`scripts/report-becker-s3-upload-completeness.js`** — streams the same `data.tar.zst` source (inventory only), lists Parquet under `{prefix}/data/` in S3, and prints missing keys, byte-size mismatches vs tar headers, per-table counts, and optional `--json` / `--fail-on-gap`.

## S3 layout (typical)

- **Parquet objects** (examples from past runs):
  - `becker/data/polymarket/{markets,trades,blocks}/…/*.parquet`
  - `becker/data/kalshi/{markets,trades}/…/*.parquet`
- **Manifests** (written by script):
  - `…/data-lake/becker-polymarket/dataset_manifest.json`
  - `…/data-lake/becker-kalshi/dataset_manifest.json`
- **Public URLs** in manifests use `publicBaseUrl` / `--public-base-url` (HTTPS base for the bucket+prefix).

## Useful CLI flags (see script header)

- `--dry-run`, `--max-files-per-table`, `--skip-existing-by-list`, `--check-existing`, `--list-s3-parquet-limit`, `--download-url`, `--public-base-url`, `--acl`, `--region`, retries, `--verbose` / `--quiet`, `--heartbeat-seconds`, etc.

## App ↔ private bucket (separate from this script)

- **Route**: `src/pages/api/data-lake/parquet.js` — server **`GetObject`**; browser calls same-origin with `?path=relative/to/prefix/file.parquet`.
- **Polymarket prefix**: `DATA_LAKE_S3_KEY_PREFIX` (e.g. ends with `…/polymarket`).
- **Kalshi prefix**: `DATA_LAKE_KALSHI_S3_KEY_PREFIX` **or** derive by replacing trailing `/polymarket` with `/kalshi` on the polymarket prefix.
- **Dataset switch**: `?lake=kalshi` uses the Kalshi prefix; default path uses polymarket prefix.
- **Client**: `NEXT_PUBLIC_DATA_LAKE_USE_S3_PROXY=true` plus bucket/region/AWS keys on the server.

## Security / ops

- **Never commit real AWS keys.** Becker CLI scripts load **repo-root `.env` / `.env.local`** via `scripts/loadRepoEnvForAws.js` (`AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID`, `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`, `AWS_REGION`). Rotate any keys that were ever committed.
- **CORS** on the bucket matters only if the **browser** fetches Parquet via **public HTTPS URLs** (not via the proxy).

## Past improvements (conversation summary)

- Streaming pipeline to avoid disk blow-up; per-file upload from tar.
- Manifest generation + S3 upload as final step (`[3/3]`).
- **Kalshi** added as a second dataset alongside Polymarket (same bucket, `kalshi/` tree + separate manifest id `becker-kalshi`).
- Placeholder vs real AWS credential detection in the script to avoid “silent” misconfiguration.

